    ----------
    attachment_id
    issue_id
    file_url
    uploaded_by

Actual files stored in object storage.

6. APIs (1 minute)
  Create Issue
  POST /projects/{projectId}/issues

  Request:
  
  {
   title: "Login Bug",
   description: "User unable to login"
  }
  Update Issue Status
  PATCH /issues/{id}/status
  Add Comment
  POST /issues/{id}/comments
  Search Issues
  GET /issues?status=OPEN&assignee=123

7. Caching (1 minute)
  Since issues are frequently read, we add Redis caching.
  Cache:
  project metadata
  issue lists
  user sessions
  
  Flow:
  
  Client
    |
  API
    |
  Redis Cache
    |
  Database
8. Handling Attachments
  Attachments may be large.
  Instead of storing them in DB:
  Store in:
  Object storage (S3)
  
  Database stores only:
  file_url
  issue_id

9. Event Driven Notifications (1 minute)
    When an issue is created:
    
    Issue Service
          |
       Kafka Queue
          |
    Notification Service
          |
    Email / Slack / Push
    
    This ensures notifications do not slow down API responses.

10. Handling Concurrency
  Multiple users may update the same issue.
  Solution:
  Optimistic locking
  Add version column.
  
  Example:
  UPDATE issues
  SET status='DONE', version=version+1
  WHERE id=1 AND version=3

If version mismatch occurs → retry.

11. Scaling the System (2 minutes)
  Horizontal Scaling
  Load Balancer
     |
  Multiple API Servers
  Database Scaling
  
  Use:
  Read Replicas
  Primary DB (Writes)
        |
  Read Replica (Reads)
  Sharding
  Shard by:
  ProjectID
  All issues of the same project go to the same shard.
  Search Scaling
    Use:
    Elasticsearch cluster

12. Potential Bottlenecks
  Heavy Search Queries
    Solution:
    Elasticsearch
  
  Large Attachments
    Solution:
    Object storage
    CDN
  
  Notification Load
    Solution:
    Kafka queue

